modules.description: Provides functions for parsing and manipulating time intervals, including duration calculations, interval merging, and overlap detection. Operates on custom time range types and timestamped events. Used to manage scheduling conflicts and compute cumulative time spans in real-time data processing pipelines.

Provides command-line argument parsing through a list of (name, spec, description) tuples, initializes runtime state, and exits the program. Processes file content by executing a provided function, copies input between file descriptors, extracts substrings from input, and reads file contents directly. Used to handle command-line arguments, manage input/output streams, and process text files in a controlled manner.
